00:27:10.070 --> 00:27:14.160
letting you, I mean, I adopted some of the ideas you got in here

00:27:14.360 --> 00:27:19.520
and some of my own, and Docker builds went so much faster.

00:27:20.740 --> 00:27:20.780
Yeah.

00:27:21.990 --> 00:27:24.340
I mean, the most important thing is to have multi-stage builds,

00:27:24.540 --> 00:27:27.680
which means that you have a separate container

00:27:27.920 --> 00:27:30.400
that builds your application, whether it's a virtual

00:27:30.490 --> 00:27:30.580
.

00:27:31.200 --> 00:27:32.760
As we said before, which I like better,

00:27:33.020 --> 00:27:34.540
or if you just build it to a directory

00:27:34.880 --> 00:27:36.160
and then somehow get it over.

00:27:38.560 --> 00:27:40.220
Because you don't want to have a C compiler

00:27:40.540 --> 00:27:43.240
in all your production containers.

00:27:43.540 --> 00:27:45.060
It's just a waste of space.

00:27:45.580 --> 00:27:47.200
And as you said, living off the land.

00:27:47.500 --> 00:27:47.960
It's not good.

00:27:50.340 --> 00:27:50.700
Then--

00:27:50.720 --> 00:27:53.360
- The hacker's into a desert, not a lush forest.

