- Exactly.

00:27:55.320 --> 00:27:56.620
I mean, they're still going to figure it out,

00:27:56.780 --> 00:27:59.920
but it's just nicer and easier to reason about.

00:28:00.200 --> 00:28:03.740
Then judicious layering makes a big difference,

00:28:03.900 --> 00:28:06.220
that you are very clear about when you build what,

00:28:06.580 --> 00:28:09.840
that you basically sort your commands in the order

00:28:10.100 --> 00:28:12.040
in that they are most likely to change.

00:28:12.800 --> 00:28:15.780
So in a build container, that means that your last step

00:28:16.120 --> 00:28:19.179
is copying the application, and the step before

00:28:19.200 --> 00:28:20.340
is copying the dependencies.

