challenge of a lot of the upgrades of a lot of the packages been like, well, that used to be bytes

00:33:36.290 --> 00:33:40.900
or strings. Now we've got to treat them differently and we've got to change that. That's the part that

00:33:40.930 --> 00:33:49.420
was really took the work. And threading seems harder than strings. I don't know. Maybe it's not.

00:33:52.120 --> 00:33:54.300
Is this going to be a big challenge for people or what do you think?

00:33:55.640 --> 00:34:00.720
Yeah, I guess we will see, right? Like normal code is probably not going to be affected a lot,

00:34:01.000 --> 00:34:04.120
